NUMBER 24
NAME Annex, OOC Area
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Here is the place to find current information on Legends.  This
room is strictly out of character and is not to be used as
a sanctuary of any kind.

The two signs here hold the new rate schedule.

Reading the two scrolls will show you the FAQ on the new rates.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT O 339
ITEM 0 1112
ITEM 1 1112
ITEM 2 540
ITEM 3 540
ITEM 4 540
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 0
Play for free until Level 10! Characters up to and including Level 9
will play for free. This gives new players plenty of time to thoroughly
acclimate themselves to the game before making a financial commitment.

After Level 9, you may still logon and your character may participate
with the game, however he or she will not develop. There will be no way
to make up for this lost experience.

Character Fees only $100/quarter! To develop a character past Level 10,
one must pay a character fee. Initial character fees will include a
prorated quarterly fee for the remainder of the current quarter (minimum
$10) and the full fee for the following quarter.

At the beginning of a new quarter all unpaid characters will have their
ability to advance interrupted. In other words, the character's
ability to earn experience points is suspended. To avoid this suspension
in character development, customers are encouraged to pay their
character fees in advance.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 1
The $100 quarterly character fee is due by the 20th of the month prior
of the start of the quarter in order to allow enough time for
processing. (Quarters start on the first of January, April, July
and October) Credit card customers will have their character
fees automatically charged to their cards on the 20th of the month
quarter unless they notify game management in advance by FAX,

There may be additional fees at various times for special online events
(quests) at the discretion of game management. Other events may be
reserved for paid characters only.

NovaLink reserves the right to discontinue, suspend or erase any
character for any reason. In this event, the pro-rata portion of any
paid character fees will be refunded by check within 60 days.

==================================================================
Special offer for existing Legends of Future Past customers: Sign-up now
and play from now until Oct. 1 Free

If the fee for the quarter starting Oct 1, 1997 is paid before then, any
time between application of payment and start of the quarter will be
free.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 2
           How Does This Affect ME?

There are many fine issues with this rate plan, and like so many things in
Legends, there are few concrete boundaries. Here, however, are some
questions that have been asked already and their answers as well as some
guidelines as to how things work.

      Do I have to pay for my 'locker character'?

Probably not. If you have a character just storing stuff for you, chances
are that he is not over level 10 and is not going to be. Characters don't
have to pay until they exceed level 10.

      I have a character that is a picker and/or smith, do I have to
pay for her?

Maybe. If she is under level 10, the character will continue to advance
until level 10 is reached, regardless. When level 10 is reached, however,
the advancement will stop. It will be up to you to decide if you want to
have her advance further. If you decide to have her, yes, you will have to
pay.

      I have a character I play now and then, do I have to pay for
him?

Maybe, it depends on how much you play him. Having a minor persona
that doesn't play much and just wanders about town and slugs a monster
or three, probably doesn't need to pay. However, if you are doing
substantial interaction, you will have to pay. As always, however, any
character at or above tenth level will not gain experience points unless a
fee is paid.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 3
      Ok, silly question, what do you mean by 'substantial
interaction'?

Substantial interaction is qualified by (and not limited to) being in the game
for more than 5 hours a month (this is NOT firm), being involved in plots
regardless of time spent online or otherwise being involved in the flow of
the game. It is safe to assume that any event, even if a special quest fee
isn't required, will be only for paid characters.

      Yeah, what about that quest fee? Will all quests have a fee?

No, in fact, most will NOT. Those quests that will have fees will be above
and beyond in some fashion. They could be on a quest beyond the
wastes, or part of a major plot that requires several GMs and much time
to put together. Either way, the game management will make sure that you
get your money's worth out of the event.

      This is cool! Where do I sign?

You notify us which characters on which accounts you wish to pay for
and please put a total on the request (If you specify 2 characters, mention
'Charge $200' somewhere.). You can do this in one of four ways:

     Phone: 800 274 2814 M-F 9-5 ET
     Email: druid@novalink.com (Make sure you use put LEGENDS in
     the subject)
     Fax: 508 836 4766
     SMail: 200 Friberg Pkwy #4003, Westborough, MA, 01581

Please allow 2 full business days to process the request.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 4
      I'm a prepaid user now. How do I convert?

Oooh, tough question. When you are ready to mail your check to us,
check your balance. Assume six days for mail to get here and be
processed, and estimate your playing time for those five days. Subtract
the amount of money for that playing from your balance, and then send us
the difference.

Example: You want to pay for two characters.

     Current balance: $-46
     Estimate playing $ 18 (10 hours)
     Balance after: $-28

     First character: $ 72 (100-28)
     Second character:$100
     Send check for $172

There will, of course, be minor descrepancies. If you overpay, we will
keep it on file for next quarter or send a check back to you. If you
underpay, we will evaluate that on a situational basis.

If you have read this carefully and still have questions, then use the email
link below to send a question to the manager. PLEASE read this carefully
before emailing, almost all answers are here.
*DESCRIPTION_END

;
