IFPREVERB LOOK 2
  IFVAR LAWBREAK > 15
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You can see that the panel has been smashed. Exposed wiring and broken pieces of buttons can be seen.
  ELSE
    IFVAR LAWBREAK < 5
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You can see a panel with several rows of numbered buttons on it.
    ELSE
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER The panel looks like it has taken a beaten.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB PUSH 2
  IFVAR LAWBREAKOUT ! 0
    IFVAR INTNUM68 > 19 ; TECHNOLOGISTS ONLY CAN FIX THE FORCIE-FIELD
      CLEARVERB
      GMMSG %n is fixing the lawkeepers panel.
      ADD INTNUM68 1
		ECHO PLAYER %cYou feel you have gained technological insight.
      EQUAL ROUNDTIME 60
      EQUAL LAWBREAKOUT 0
      EQUAL LAWBREAK 0
      STRCVT 0 ROUNDTIME
      ECHO PLAYER You begin to rewire the broken controls...
      ECHO PLAYER [Round: %0 seconds]
      ECHO OTHERS %n goes to work on the smashed panel..
      PLREVENT 5
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO PLAYER You connect some more wires and test out a few buttons.
      ECHO OTHERS %n continues to work on the smashed panel.
      PLREVENT 5
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO PLAYER You hook up the last wire, and something shorts out.
      ECHO OTHERS %n makes a few more connections, and a spark or two flies out of the panel.
      PLREVENT 5
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO PLAYER You make a final connection, and everything seems to work fine.
      ECHO OTHERS %n finishes with the repairs and begins to put the panel back into place.
      PLREVENT 5
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO PLAYER Finished, you put the last screw back into place.
      ECHO OTHERS %n finishes re-attaching the panel.
    ELSE
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You make an attempt to fix the smashed panel, but realize quickly that you lack the technological training.
      ECHO OTHERS %n makes an attempt to fix the smashed panel, but can't seem to figure out what to do.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
